&lt;p data-start=&quot;1913&quot; data-end=&quot;1968&quot; data-is-last-node=&quot;&quot; data-is-only-node=&quot;&quot;&gt;Join us in building the power foundation of the future!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;708&quot; data-end=&quot;728&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;708&quot; data-end=&quot;728&quot;&gt;Role Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;708&quot; data-end=&quot;728&quot;&gt;In this role, you will lead the control architecture and system behavior of advanced AC-DC and DC-DC power conversion platforms across low- and medium-voltage applications. You will define and drive control strategies for complex converter topologies, including multilevel and resonant systems. As a Staff engineer, you will own system-level control decisions, set technical direction across programs, and ensure performance targets are achieved from concept through production. You will work across modeling, digital control development, embedded implementation, hardware integration, and validation to deliver robust, scalable, high-performance power conversion solutions. You will also mentor engineers and raise the technical standard of the control organization&lt;/p&gt;
